8
[div class=p 
	(dailymotion|v=xevwa8|w=320|h=240)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It all started with a simple question. "Do you think you could complete a Sonic game without collecting a single ring?"
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Three years, two GMVs and one echidna later, the end result is here for all to see.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This run is performed on a hacked version of Sonic 1, allowing the player to play as Knuckles, which Sega should've been able to let you do back in 1994. The official thread for the game is 
	[a class=extlink href=http://info.sonicretro.org/Knuckles_the_Echidna_in_Sonic_the_Hedgehog rel=nofollow 
		"here
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Rundescription 
	" Run description
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This run has three main goals. They're a bit like the three laws of robotics in that they're dependent on each other. They are:
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		" Avoid all rings, and any other items that would permit me to take damage (shield, invincibility)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Don't fly over the top (or zip to the end) of the level because that would be boring (thanks CrazyTerabyte), except where not doing so would force you to collect rings
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Fastest time given the above two conditions
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[div class=p 
	"and other criteria:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Takes no damage (obviously)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Ignores delays caused by bonus effects
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Abuses programming errors in the game
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Makes speed/entertainment tradeoffs
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Is a concept demo
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Given that the focus of the movie was already not going to be blindly speeding through the game, I felt the second point was necessary to make the best movie. Otherwise you'd just be climbing over the whole of Marble Zone which looks clever once, but boring after that.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Emulatorinformation 
	" Emulator information
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Gens 9.5b was used to record this run. At times I also used Upthorn's hacked-specifically-for-Sonic-1 version, which proved intriguing without being essential.
	$LF
]div
